race.comment: MUMMSIE (5) is fitter for three runs back and looks well placed here. Blinkers added and worth noting her sole career win was at this journey. PENDANTE (3) has been racing well including a strong on-speed win over 2000m last time. Little more weight but in form and same claimer aboard. Will take catching. GREATESTOFEASE (4) has been going better than form suggests and just got too far back at Halidon last time. Claim helps and drawn to be close stalking the pace. WHERE YA BEAN (1) has been in good form over shorter races and looks well placed stepping out further in journey now. Has a win and a placing from two tries at the journey. BRASSI ROAD (6) placed in easier company at the picnics last time. Could sneak a place again.
